ZTEX is a manufacturer of FPGA boards. ZTEX offers 
[USB-FPGA Modules 1.15y](http://www.ztex.de/usb-fpga-1/usb-fpga-1.15y.e.html) with four Spartan 6 LX150 and 
[USB-FPGA Modules 1.15x](http://www.ztex.de/usb-fpga-1/usb-fpga-1.15x.e.html) with a single Spartan 6 LX150
which are optimized for cryptographic computations like Bitcoin Mining. 

These FPGA Board have on-board voltage regulators and an USB controller which is used for
communication and device programming. Low cost
FPGA mining rigs can be build using standard components (USB hubs, USB cables, ATX PSU's).

With the current version of the [[BTCMiner]] an average hash rate of about 215 MH/s per FPGA can be achieved. Power dissipation is 9.8 W at 216 MHz.

Current prices including volume prices are stated at the [Bitcoin Forum](https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=49180).

